name:                about
stack:               ( -- )
return stack:        ( -- )
string stack:        ( -- )
category:
input stream:        word name

decription:          reads a word from input stream, which is appended to
                     a (currently hardcoded) dir $doc, then used as path/file
                     of a file whose contents are displayed. Ideally "word" is
                     the name of an existing yoda word, which has already been
                     described ("documemented"), in which case will the displayed
                     file containing some informative descriptions.

contexts:            interpreting, compiling

example:             about about

notes:               similar do doc, with the difference that file isn't opened in
                     an editor, but its contents merely displayed.
